        <item>
            <title>Introducing Kotlin/Wasm</title>
            <link>/introducing-kotlin-wasm/</link>
            <pubDate>Sat, 25 Mar 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            
            <guid>/introducing-kotlin-wasm/</guid>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;This blog post is a refined transcription of the presentation Zalim Bashorov and I gave at &lt;a href=&#34;https://wasm.io/&#34;&gt;Wasm I/O&lt;/a&gt; 2023 to introduce &lt;a href=&#34;http://kotl.in/wasm/&#34;&gt;Kotlin/Wasm&lt;/a&gt;. The recording is also available on &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LCtMC_IVCKo&#34;&gt;YouTube&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;intro&#34;&gt;
  Intro
  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#intro&#34;&gt;
    &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://seb.deleuze.fr/images/wasmio23/slide1.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Zalim&lt;/strong&gt; Hi, everyone! I’m &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/bashorov&#34;&gt;Zalim&lt;/a&gt;. I’m writing Kotlin in Kotlin at JetBrains and leading Kotlin/Wasm. We are going to have a quick journey around Kotlin/Wasm. We will see what the possibilities there are and also have a look at the inside.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
        </item>
        
